(37, 'en', 'Md. Ashraf Hossen ', 'Jessore', '15th December 1952', '976', '0403010924', 'Not Found', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahinee', 'M. A. Manjur', '<p>MD. Ashraf Hossen was born in Satiantala village in curamanakathi Union of Sadar Upazila of Jessore in respectable Muslim family in 15th December 1952. He is the father of 5 children. During the war, fought with great &nbsp;valor in Sector 8. His Gazette No. 976, War ID No. 0403010924, and the Ministry Certificate No. No. M-115499.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the highlights of the conversation follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities</strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Md. Ashraf Hossen, Father: late Anwar Hossen, Mother: Late Shurmana Bibi. &nbsp;Address: Satiantala, curamanakathi, Jessore Sadar, Jessore. I fought in Sector 8. The sector commander was Major M A Manzur. I&rsquo;m a village doctor. I used to study before the war</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participation in the war and operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Year of 1971.&nbsp; On that time East Bengal Regiment Was in Jessore Cantonment. In 1971 before 25 March they were in training in our area. In 29 March they were returning. At night of 29 March, Pakistan Army attacked on East Bengal Regiment when they were unarmed. On that time, soldiers of East Bengal Regiment&nbsp; broke the arsenal and brought some Weapons. As they were in hurry, they couldn&rsquo;t bring much Weapons and ammunition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At that time I was a student of Cantonment College and I&rsquo;ve faced all this. When they were doing this I was helping them to carry the weapons to the Kazi Nazrul Islam College. First we gave a barricade in Hoybatpur village. When west Pakistan came with the huge force we started to turn back. Though we were in shorts of Weapons and ammunition we tried our best to defense. Again we gave a barricade in front of Kaligonz upozilla. There we build a resistance with a combination of EPR, ANSAR, ARMY, volunteer and students. Because of Pakistan Army&rsquo;s force we had to turn back again and many got martyrdom. Stampeding from there we took position at Bishoykhai in Jhenidha. There we had a fierce fighting for 7-8 days. We couldn&rsquo;t tale them because of our insufficient heavy weapons.&nbsp; After stampeding again we evaded into India. First we take shelter on youth club. After medical treatment we were sent to Bihar,Chaklia, and many other places for higher training. After finishing the training we were sent to the country with weapons as guerrilla fighter. Then we started to fight in various war field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mentionable, we had a fierce fight with Pakistan Army in Shajiali bajar,Churamonkhati. This time they ran away. Then we spread everywhere as&nbsp; guerrilla.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Heartbreaking story:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At the end of the war, there was a fierce fight between the allies and enemy&nbsp; in Moshiur Nagar. Me and other fighters joined them. At a time, we all were out of shots. So we started hand combat. Many were killed there. My friend Altaf got martyrdom there. We buried him under a tree in Jogonnathpur. On that battle, our enemy were defeated and ran away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During the war, we passed the night sleepless.&nbsp; We couldn&rsquo;t sleep properly. We had to guard ourshelves. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reason for going to the Liberation War:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pakistani hates Bengali a lot. It was seen that , even we passes them, they started to mocking us in Urdu. They didn&rsquo;t want to see us. Eventually , when I was in Cantonment College, during the assembly I touched a Pakistani boy unfortunately but his obscenities to me is no match for anything. So I thought, if this country didn&rsquo;t liberated then there will be no existence of us. There is a huge distance between east and West Pakistan. So they couldn&rsquo;t be together.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our wealth was drained to West Pakistan. We didn&rsquo;t get any equitable part from there. Majority of them job here.&nbsp; We Bengali were appointed in low class job.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We engaged in the war for the liberty of this country, to get a new flag and to build a new nation, to get all kind of facilities in every sphere of our life. In this war my great contribution is, that I fought for my Motherland and became a part of this independent Bangladesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expectation to the young generation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>My Expectation to the young generation is, we independent our country by sacrificing a lot of lives.&nbsp; So they should conduct Bangladesh in such a way that we can stand high in the world.</p>\r\n', '37.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DDUh3Ods52E', 2, '1481217491', '2016-12-08'),
(38, 'en', 'Mohammad Abdus Sattar', 'Jessore', '7th August 1992', '974', '0403010954', 'Not Found', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahinee', 'M. A. Manjur', '<p>Mohammad Abdus Sattar was born in a village of curamanakathi Union of Sadar Upazila of Jessore Bhagalpur (sajiyali) in a respectable Muslim family 195 August 7. He is the father of 3 children. During the war, fought with great valor in Sector 8.His Gazette No. 974, War ID No. 0403010954,and the Ministry of muktibarta Certificate No. M-7731.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the highlights of the conversation follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mohammad Abdus Sattar,Father: Late Surat Ali, Mother: Late Manda Shundori , Address: &nbsp;Bhagalpur (sajiyali), curamanakathi, Jessore Sadar, Jessore. I fought in Sector 8. The sector commander was Major &nbsp;MA Manzur. I currently work in agriculture. I&rsquo;ve two daughters and one son.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participation in the war and operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before the war I was a student I used to study. Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was not given to the country or the Bengalis of West Pakistani army has power to try to protect the rights of the people of this country karalatakhana CIT for any given election, but he was not done. And when they declared war on 7 March speech of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman was freed from subservience to respond, and we go to India for training. One night 10-12 of us were out of the house to go. First when we were 5 that was the month of summer and on that month we reached Bongay at afternoon. Then we heard the news that Talikhola camp will not make any admission today and we have to come tomorrow morning. Then the next morning when we went there, there was Matiur Rahman told us that this day no admission will go on and told us to come on 20. He also said that there is no place to camp and have started to show a lot of problems. When we come to the main road with a despair mood then on that an Indian major stop his bike to see us. Asked our identity, we said that we are from JoyBangla. He said, &#39;Where did you go to? We said that we were here to join Talikhola Freedom Fighter camp. Asked us why we were going without joining? We are told that there will not be admitted before the date 20. Then he became very angry and said to us that all of you come with me, I will admit you. Then he brought us to Motiur Rahman and told him to admit us. Matiur Rahman said that, I will fill them at 10am. In the meantime, we went to take a shower, and the two stayed there. Then we come to the end of the bath, and I could not get them to go before 9 am. We saw that they had been admitted.&nbsp; But he was promised, not to make any admission before 10 am.&nbsp; When we stand in front of the gate, then&nbsp; Matiur Rahman Sahib came. Then we went to him and said that two of us have admitted. We were in the shower so we came late. Then Motiur Rahman said with a little bit anger that he will admit us at 2 pm. We waited there until two. Altaf, one of us wanted to go with us. He, however, did not go that day, the next day he was. And we are also standing there in line for admission. About 20 people was there but he did not admit us and told us to come on 20. Then I came out of there with their and start work inside with the trained fighters. Then we went to the capabariya camp in September-October and admitted there. We were there 3 months training. We train there with several arms and weapons. Then, when the Jessore was liberated, we were left from camp with a clearance, and said to enter. Then we went inside to look for the war criminals and our people. Then the enemy surrender and Bangladesh got victory on 16 December.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We fought for 3 days in Shajiali village. On that time the war criminals destroyed and looted a lot and raped many. We tried our best to raise resistant against them. One day we fought with war criminal in Hybotpur village. When we attacked the war criminal in hoybotpur village many of them were killed and injured.&nbsp; We also destroyed their camp. &nbsp;&nbsp;When we attacked Shatmile camp of war criminals they cried for sympathy but we couldn&rsquo;t forget that what had they done with our family and people. I think they did much loss to our country than the Pakistan Army. They showed them the way to attack us. When we fought at Gouripur&nbsp; one of our freedom fighter Altaf got martyrdom. There was a tank of them , we destroyed that.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One day a group of war criminal attacked our house but couldn&rsquo;t catch us. They looted our house, made some firing and tortured my two brothers a lot. When the Freedom Fighters started firing from a side they started to run away and took their position on the road of SHAMNAGAR all day long. Then they entered into Shajiali village and we fought all day. Then they started to show their back. But they came to our and other side villages in every week. They had a thought that Freedom Fighter were here in this village. As a result they tortured the people a lot. But their wish didn&rsquo;t came true. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reason for going to the Liberation War:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When the Pakistani army&#39;s indiscriminate attacks on innocent people, torture, murder and repression started in front of us, we could not accept the view and we participated in the liberation war</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As a freedom fighter my demands to the new generation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a freedom fighter my demands to the new generation is that, they live a fair life, not to addict in drugs, make a terrorist free nation, and they do not say a word against the patriot or the freedom fighters</p>\r\n', '38.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tsaKv-8-nUM', 1, '1481217992', '2016-12-08'),
(39, 'en', 'MD Shamsul Haque', 'Jessore', '13th November 1952', '479', '0403010960', '0405011043', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahinee', 'M. A. Manjur', '<p>MD Shamsul Haque was born in a religious Muslim family 13<sup>th</sup> November 1952 in a village Shamnagor(Sajiali) which situated at Churamonkathi upzilla in Jessore Sadaor,Jessore. He has five children. In the Liberation war he fought in sector 8 with bravery. His gadget number: 479, war ID number: 0403010960, Muktibarta number: 0405011043 and Ministry certificate Number: M-70150.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here some information about him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>MD Shamsul Haque, Father&rsquo;s name: Late Ansar Ali Biswas, Mother&rsquo;s name: Late Sahiron Nesa, Address: Shamnagor(Sajiali), Churamonkathi,Jessore Sadar,Jessore. I fought in sector 8 in war. Sector commander&rsquo;s name was Major M A Manjur. I had a job before now retired. I have 3 boys and 2 daughter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participate in war and Operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 1971, Bhangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman delivered his historic&nbsp;speech. After hearing his speech, all people of our union came out in the street. They came out such a way that they brought whatever they got in their hand like knife,stick etc. for&nbsp; taking control over the cantonment. In that day, if the PAK army came out in the road with their weapon, I am afraid there were no men left in Jessore. Really it was an extraordinary speech from Bangabandhu. I could not explain you the excitement. After that I went to Biramman bazar which was over the field of Jessore Science and Technology University.There was a chamber of Khalil Doctor. There were some of young boys whose read in class Ten in that time, we met up for going to take participate in Liberation war. But matter of regret that, we left home in the morning, my father forced me to come back home about 3-4 miles away from our house. Because I was only one child of my father. Few days later, I married a girl form nearby village Dawlatdiya, chauramonkathi. She was so young in age. My father thought that if I got married then I would not go to war.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2<sup>nd</sup> time when I visited my father in law&rsquo;s house, the road was so risky of being caught.so I took the road Poltadanga which is go through to the Churamonkathi market. But I was so unlucky. That time the rajakars were in duty in the same road that I took. Two of rajakars caught me after see alone. They had rifle and boot in their foot. In one side was train line and other side rajakars kept tramping. In front there was road where the Pak army&rsquo;s car was marching. They took me there. There was a bridge in dawlatdiya and I got someone there. I told him that I am new here in tarafdar house.Recently I got married here and I don&rsquo;t know any name here and also no one know me yet. I only know my father in law name. I told him to send this news to my father in law house. The news not only go to my father in law house but also to my family. In that day they pushed me to the Kazi Nazrul Islam College and tortured me badly. They asked me many questions from morning 9 o&rsquo;clock to 5 o&rsquo;clock at afternoon. But they didn&rsquo;t released me. One boy of the rajakars told that there was no fighter in that area. They still didn&rsquo;t want to release me. There was a man worked beside the bridge, they took him to me and asked if I know him or not. I told them I don&rsquo;t know him and the man might not know me. Then I frequently told them my father in law&rsquo;s name is Meherab Ali Tofadar and he is good man. After a long time they took reference and released me. Then I came back to my home.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>My family member started mourning while I was away. In that time some people took preparation for joining in the war. In the meantime my uncle returned home after finishing his training. Gradually more group returned. Most of the time 8-10 fighter stayed at my home. My father helped them and arranged all their needing. My family hid their weapon in day time and brought back in night. I always stay with them. One of them fighter whose name was Altaf. He was so nice and beautiful at look. He and his friend always stick each other like gum. They were from same house. Sometimes the fighters left weapon in our house and went for operation. All of a sudden a collision took place in Sajiakhali. Then we told that it is the high time to go for war. When we went out we saw that Gazi Ragab, Montu (zilla commander), they were at that place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>That time I took two sets of bullet, rifle and tightened my lungi to join in Sajiali war&rsquo;s place. Now there is a fire camp and we turned to left. Another group took position in right side. We fought from morning 9 AM to evening 7 PM face to face. Then we turned back. We could not stay at our home. So I came with my uncle Abdul khalek and went to komlapur&rsquo;s lake and took place beside the lake. We two have only two grenades and we hide the rifle in the side of lake. In the morning we saw that a crowd towards to us. We got frightened that they might caught us. But we were able to run from komlapur to kutalipur towards Sayedpur and went so far. After that we came to learn that was the group of fighter whose was from Faridpur. The Pak army killed Idris in Mathurapur after that war.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I was not afraid of them. I took part in big operation with whose was at my house. They always kept me in their touch. In this time, there was an electric tower in Churamonkathi, A group of Altaf, hafijur Rahman dulu, Abdul khalek was led by Altaf total 10 of them. We crossed Mathuapur and bombed theat tower. The bomb was so heavy that a lot of fire and sounds created and the Rajakar started firing from Satmile. But we were in stuck and could not manage to come back. Then we started running through the Jhonjhon&rsquo;s ghat and returned back. Within a months, 100 of rajakar surrendered to us. Then Altaf forbidden me to go anywhere just to stay here.But I insist to go with them and told him that I also the flame of freedom fighter as like you. Then we two or three of group start journey in the dark night. In road we saw some people and they told themselves that they caught us to Pak army. Then we walked through to Dhanurhat. We saw a lot of refugee crossed the border line. We rested in that school for night. In morning we went to the ghat and found a boat. I, Abdul Rahim and may be the name is Gafur (martyr) ride on the boat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then I slowly crossed the river. Then we went directly Chapabariya camp and got admitted. Then within 1 month we gain our freedom.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I always keep my eye to the fighter and watch their activities so carefully that most of us don&rsquo;t know about that. Attack to the Rajakar, the chaiman of peace committee and night operation, I took part myself with the fighter. 10-15 fighters stay in our house and we out for after evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What I want as freedom fighter to new generation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a freedom fighter I just want that Bangladesh which is liberated by the lead of Bagabandhu, the father of our nation, is get more beautiful by the new generation of our country. Taking good care everything is a duty of new generation.</p>\r\n', '39.jpg', '	https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BhEfXksT13A', 5, '1481218298', '2016-12-08'),
(40, 'en', 'Mohammad Daud Hossain', 'Jessore', '21 August, 1944 ', '467', '0403010902', '0405010793', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahinee', 'M. A. Manjur', '<p>Mohammad Daud Hossain was born on 21 August, 1944 in Khitibdiya village in Churamankathi Union of Sadar Upazila of Jessore in a respectable Muslim family. He is the father of two children. During the war, fought with great valor in Sector 8. His Gazette No. 467, War ID No. 0403010902, Muktibarta No: 0405010793 and the Ministry of Certificate No. M -15303. Some of the highlights of the conversation follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mohammad Daud Hossain, Father: Late Shamser Mollah, Mother: Late Khojeda Begum, Address:&nbsp; Khitibdiya, churamankathi, Jessore Sadar, Jessore. I fought in Sector 8. The sector commander was Major M A Manzur. By profession I am a rickshaw driver. I have one son, one daughter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participation in the war and operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I go to the war later a month. I come to the Churamankathi market and see, the Pakistani army is taking over our peoples and carring the rail line on the car.I also carried then gave me two bread that i ate. Then i went into the house for feeling of appetite where my parents are stayed. It was market day I came home from the market, there are 8 to 10 people, and there are many collaborators. Collaborators stay on post office at the top of a weapon, I&#39;m going to run away with a straight run to the Daulatadiya took the rifle away and crossed the train road to go to Kamlapur where our fighters are stayed and i involved with them.Then they told me that you went to India. I went to sector 8 to Mr.Huda of India. Mr. Huda told me that you have any community, then I told that i have no community but i became a member of Ansar Bahini.Then he said that you know everything. And he said to me, then you open your rifle, and enfold. I did everything then he told that you do not need to go anywhere else you stay in Riyar. Further Mr. Huda said that, you go to them with a rifle. I went to a place called Chaugachha Kadamtala where there was tempestuous fighting. I became-two-man that means L, M, G two. Because Maxim and rifle was in my hand. From there I could not cross the river because of the L, M, G and Maxim was on my shoulder.I dismounted the Maxim down the water and I got left out of the place.Then Seikhera stayed there and i&nbsp; saw that there are two people died. I come there and told them that the two soldier&rsquo;s died.Then those two corpsing are brought on shoulder. Again then came back to India. Then, at the border to fight Punjabis could go to other side to fight at the border. There are three Punjabis out of three Punjabis one of living and two died. That night after the body of the two to inhume that did not give in India again came back in Bangladesh and at 3 nights at the two corpsings are inhumed in same hole. This time we went back again to the camp. When we went back to the camp and told us what are you doing? We said that we did this is anything.Then told us that you take bath and after completing bath eating some bread. Then again told us that had to go to war again, and said that there was a registry office was on the upper storey of two-shade that should be burst by grenade. Then this two-shade was burst. Some days later told us that we will go back today the country. The first came in that night, the night is the first independent of Bangladesh in the circuit house where Mr. Huda Saheb attended. Huda told us that you will not eat anything from any source and we are feeling so much appetite almost we were dieing and will not go to any side from the wall. When I started to go quietly at the base of one of the machine then a small candle burning in the house and I thought that what is this place and why is smoking? Then a boy was with me from Faridpur, his name was Chandu. I said Chandu that you stand inside the gate I came to see that what is the thing? I went with the weapons and see that the how much rice flour and how much oil there is, again, how many goats tied and how much meat keep on the stove and making the bread with rearrange but do not eat anyone.I am thinking that i felt very hungry so give me poision oil else other things.Again thinking that we will die with fighting then two loaves of bread from the inside out and I have inserted the byalca in the waves a little from inside of meat stove to take a little soup ate two tondur bread. Then after eating the bread and told that come to see what is burning that room. Then he told me that why will you go to there what will happen or not? Then i told that i shall go to see and come back, oneday i shall die and riding on the two-shades. I look down the floor to see that the gun that is like Bengalis gun.Then again riding the two-shades to see that how much Pakistanis weapons there that are not calculation.Such of them big big shot, rifle and stimgun. Then i slowly got down and said Chandu these happen in there. After I went into the house of Major Huda and said that sir, I went to one place, and saw the things.Then sir said that plant the duty plant the duty does not let anyone else use one and said that anyone can not rise Why did you go? I told that sir i come back to see when die, do not die that is not right. After then night cross to morning then planted the duity that place.Then we went to duty and sir told that you go to railgate we went to all. We all to go and see a lot of people are crying during the night Jessore has become independent at around at night 12. When asked them why, they said that Punjabis and Biharis raped our mothers and sisters and killed a lot of people. How many people killed then said that a lot of people killed. Then asked them that who are killed them and then they said that come with us then we introduce them.Then go to see that and thought that any weapon remain his and he can kill us and later 3-4 of us told to come out who are remain. Then come out of the 16 people with children and male and female. Then checked out of the 16 people who like to be told that this is all one side. He said there was another one of our brave men that they all train lines on the road.Then given them a line L, M, G Brush had come to an end. Then everybody went from there. Two days after the 3-day train accident happened that the Jessore. A lot of people had died there. We all went to come back cantonment from and gave us a room and said, go to the in that house.We stayed in that house for about in a month, and only do the duty. Then go to the bank and see that money and money there is no any lack of money. After see that car came of Sikider and the money goes to take the car.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When Jessore becomes independent after 15 days Bhaitapara village of Lohagara Thana is not independent. So we went to Bhaitaparay.There I have not eaten for three days. Just going out to fight and fight. We seemed to seven days after they salendar. We hold them made the handover in the cantonment. I&#39;m proud as a freedom fighter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reason to go to the War:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I went to the war in this country is an independent, sovereign state and the right to self-determination and to establish the common people of this country to the realization of the right to fair.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As a freedom fighters demand to a new generation: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As a freedom fighters demand to a new generation that we have a lot of labor, starvation, hunger, war, sacrifice and taste for the country, for the freedom of the people who brought you your freedom away to protect your personal duties.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '40.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qFJEhqikqlw', 3, '1481220289', '2016-12-08'),
(41, 'en', 'Md Hafizur Rahman Mallick', 'Jessore', 'January 9, 1950', '987', '0403010956', 'Not Found', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahinee', 'M. A. Manjur', '<p>Md Hafizur Rahman Mallick was born on January 9, 1950 a respectable Muslim family of chatiyantala village in&nbsp; churamankathi union of Sadar&nbsp; Upazila of Jessore town. He is the father of 1 child. During the war, fought with great valor in Sector 8. His Gazette No. 987, and the Ministry of War ID No. 0403010956 Certificate No. M-95020. Some of the highlights of the conversation follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Md. Hafizur Rahman Mallick, father of the deceased Ibrahim Mallick, mother certified dead Jabeda Khatun, Address chatiyantala, churamankathi, Jessore Sadar, Jessore. I fought in Sector 8. The sector commander was Major MA Manzur. By profession I am a farmer by profession. I have only one son.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participation in the war and operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In 1971 when began the riot, the East Bengal Regiment Jessore Cantonment. Then the time in the morning is a battle and a lot of Bengali fighters were killed in the war. Our home in Chatiyantala village near in Cantonment. Army came there by afraid. Major Anwar Hossain died there. Nazrul Islam College is inhumed him. There is his tomb.This situation our dwelling is burnt .Then we wander here and there. After we took our family far away in the village. From there we have lead our life a lot of trouble. Then the war left a plan. Then we&#39;ll go to in a body to give the name in freedom fighters, talikhola camps in India and youthcamp.<br />\r\nBy the end of training from there we return our country. When started fighting, we stayed in Khojarhat. The Punjabi soldiers come away, then we have four of them insisted. We took over a deserted place. They tell us we feel hungry, so give us to eat. Then we offer them a home, cooking a meal that we give them to eat. After eating, we tell them to do syalendar but they did not. Then we let them pile up. They pushed us beside in a green room to enter by the next door. First, they charge us a grenede a boy takes an eye. Then the eyes are blind. Then we give the fire, the three men were killed and another survived. Another stayed in house, after we insisted with his bundle and swamp him the river by shot put.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I remember many events of the war. Yes read, because I see many Punjabis are killed people, and at time time of operation we have also killed the people. These are remembering. At that time, many of our relatives have died. Since our home near the cantonment, so many people were killed here. Fighting became our country in nine months. We had to fight like a half-month time. We did the biggest operation at pulerhat. Such of the smallest operation, in Sathmail markets were war criminals camp. There was a fighting there with them. From there they (war criminals) went away.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We are very happy after independence the country. Because of becoming the independence that is a lot of pleasure to us. Because I wanted to be the liberation of Bangladesh, Bangladesh&#39;s people live in an independent country. By the respond call of Bangobondhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, we are all fighters today. We have got independence the country by him. Today we found it our witness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>As a freedom fighters demand to a new generation: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, almost at the end of the freedom fighters, freedom fighters majority of 60-70 year-old age. This came at the end of the freedom to do what they will, but they are close, they&#39;d better be the country&#39;s youth, the youth of the country should work. But the youth today is chaotic, then they can not be expected by some of the country. So understood the youth society, had to convince so that they took the country forward. They are the future citizens of the country so they will control the country.</p>\r\n', '41.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rkNgHmQTrG0', 7, '1481220643', '2016-12-08'),
(42, 'en', 'Md Shahidul Islam', 'Jessore', '15 October,1954', '2152', 'Not Found', 'Not Found', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahini', 'Mejor M A Monjur', '<p>Md Shahidul Islam born in a religious Muslim family 15 October 1954 in a village Mahadia at the union of Chachra in Jessore Sadar. He has one child. In the liberation war, he fought in sector 8 with great bravery. His gadget no: 2152, Indian welfare trust no: 25320 and ministry certificate no: M-195739.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here is some of the discussion about him:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identity:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; MD Shahidul Islam, Father&rsquo;s name: Late Golam Hossein Khan, Mother&rsquo;s name: Late Johurenessa, Address: Mahadia, Chachara,Jessore Sadar,Jessore. I fought in sector 8 in the war. Sector commander was M A Manjur. I was the driver of Commander Manjur in war. I have one son.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participate in war and Operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 1971, 27<sup>th</sup> March Marshall&rsquo;s house give us a fixed time and we went on that time. Then we stayed in Malancho. Then EPR took us and kept under their shelter. When we heard the Bangabandhu Speech, we determined that we are close to liberated. Bengali police, answer and all of Bengali whispering that we were about to liberated. I was at malancho. East Bengal regiment, BDB, EPR, all are Bengali. They gave me the car. None of them can drive. So I was the driver and I drive them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then we went Navaran, and then Benapole. The Pak Army was marching in front but we gradually move back warding. Also exchanged firing. I was driving. In the car, there was ammo and EPR. But they moved first and we retreated, went to India. In India, we had to report in first writer building. After reporting, they gave us shelter in a tin shed house. We stayed in that room for that night. Next morning, we saw that everybody went to Mujibnagar. There was a meeting of forming government board. Then we had a deal with India and Russia.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We visited Chapabari, Ranaghat,Majdi and Talikhola camp. We had to feed them, shelter them, and took them for training. I saw many fights in front of my eyes. There was a place name Chatal , there died many people. Sheikh Majibur Rahman was our inspiration. After his speech, we were set out for a fight. But the Pak army kept torturing with the marshall&rsquo;s law. A long fight took nine months, we fight in Guerilla system. Lots of lives, wealth were wasted. We could not able to make list how many have died. But we tried to count and delivered to our commander Major Manjur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The reason for fighting:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To make a beautiful country,beautiful mind,and giving the right to all people, we fought for our country. Also, all foreign help went for the Pakistan. That&#39;s the way we fought.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Contribution:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Actually, I was a driver and I have to stick with Major Manjur.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What I get after fighting:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>I get a lot of things. We have varsity, college, safety road, electricity. Gradually country is going to self-contained.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request to the new generation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We fought for living a peaceful country. We just want that we can live peacefully and make this country more beautiful.</p>\r\n', '42.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=o5ZTGrO0Q94', 2, '1481335399', '2016-12-09'),
(43, 'en', 'MD. Akhter Hussein Chaklader', 'Jessore', '4 January, 1955', '200', '0403010941', 'Not Found', 'Sector 8', 'Muktibahini', 'Mejor M A Monjur', '<p>MD. Akhter Hussein Chaklader was born in Khitibdia village in curamanakathi Union of Sadar Upazila of Jessore-7408 in respectable Muslim family on 4 January 1955. He is the father of 4 children. During the war, fought with great valour in Sector 8. His Gazette No. 200, Freedom Fighters ID No. 0403010941 and the Ministry Certificate No. M-79558. Some of the highlights of the conversation follow:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Identities:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>MD. Akhter Hussein Chaklader, Father: late Adil Uddin Chaklader, Mother: Late Rahela Begum. &nbsp;Address: Khitibdia, curamanakathi, Jessore Sadar, Jessore. I fought in Sector 8. The sector commander was Major M A Manzur and sub-sector commander was Major Mr Huda. I was an Ansar commander before the liberation war. I was an employee in Registry Office. I&rsquo;ve 3 sons and 1 daughter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Participation in the war and operation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We left at the primary stage of the war. My house was near to the Jessore Cantonment. I supported the First Bangle Regiment. In Monday I worked as a contractor for first Bangle. First Bangle was at Jogonnathpur beside my father in law house. On that time Pakistan military took off 150 bangles of the first bangle. So we told the CO about this. He was a captain of BDR. He told that they had to follow some rules and regulations. They came on Monday night and next morning a tremendous war started. Some of us came to the railway station. Coming here we saw a man who had been shot at the leg and dead. When we were ready to bury the dead body, we saw those first bangles were running towards us. When Pakistan military started firing, we took the body on the shoulder and buried the dead body near a bridge. After buried the body we came to Shatmile School. &nbsp;A man from Bengali gave us 2 pieces of bread and 2 pieces of sweet to eat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Then we came into Shabashpur crossing the railway bridge, we reached Chougacha through Abdulpur. When we reached there we joined with our EPR. We defenced with them. We heard that Pakistan army killed many people in Sholua. Hearing this we crossed the river and went to the Muslim EPR camp. In Muslim camp we were sitting in a bus. On that time Panjabi entered into India. Entering India they killed 2 men and saw the Indian flag. All men were running. Even BSF was running with people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In 10 minutes mortars firing started in Kuroli. From there we walked to Bonga. Reaching there admitted into the camp on the first day. We were sent to Captain Mukharje&rsquo;s camp after one week of our entry. We saw him to study a file. After one week, in one evening we were given 3 or 4 breads one quarter of sugar and told to pack up. We packed up everything and we stood in a line. Then we reached Bonga station crossing Hatia again. Calling the name, each 45 entered into a bogy. At 11 pm train started. As it was a coal engine train, the engine was replaced in Domdom. &nbsp;Next day we reached at 11 pm. We saw Indian cars at a line. We got into the car. Each 45 got into one car. There were 100 cars. As the car was driving on the hills and zigzag road, some of us started crying.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally we reached EPR camp. There was a cornel; a major and a captain were standing. They asked me where I was from. I answered &nbsp;&nbsp;that I was from Jessore. Then they gave me 17&rdquo; bed sheet and one cup and one plate. They gave us food to eat.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the next morning, we were ordered to stand in a line. They made me commander and told me what to do. On the first day, we built 1600 toilets for Indian army and bangle regiment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>They gave us Stain gun training first. After half an hour, again a doctor came and taught us some primary work for treatment. After half an hour, whistle blown away and an engineer came to us and&nbsp;&nbsp; told us to open our books and papers. Then he taught us how to destroy rail line, bridge, and culvert. After 28 days training, we were sent off to Kollan. We stayed there for 2 days. Next day, we went out for a visit. After returning, we saw minimum 50 bus of Bangladesh. Then we get in quickly. There was a full loaded truck with weapons. Army&rsquo;s cars were all around us. We were brought to Boyra. Coming here each 11 people made a group and entered into Bangladesh. We came to Kasipur and my duty was near the major&rsquo;s car. One day a war took place after we came. We left 4 tanks and placed 11 tanks. We were bombing at Kamarkhali Bridge. Then we all entered into the cantonment. We went to the canteen, cinema hall, and white steam quarter. Reaching there Indian military started to loot everything. Then we went to the new market. After that, major ordered us to go Girdonkhali quickly. Next, we joined in the militia. There we were given 60 takas and certificate by Mr Osmani.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expectation to the young generation:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You guys are our children. You will be with us and talk about us. You will build this country beautifully. You will protect the country. We brought the country now it&rsquo;s your time to protect it.</p>\r\n', '43.jpg', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xxUTsaOlLSs', 1, '1481425094', '2016-12-10');

