(1, 'en', 'Sector 1', '<p><img alt="sector 1" src="img/sector/sector-1.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />Chittagong District,&nbsp;Chittagong Hill Tracts, and the entire eastern area of the&nbsp;Noakhali District&nbsp;on the banks of the river Muhuri. The headquarters of sector 1 was at Harina. 10,000 of freedom fighters was fighting in this sector. Among them was the EPR, police, army, navy and air force, nearly two thousand regular troops, and there were about eight thousand Gono-bahini. This group of 137 guerrillas were sent inside the country.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Major&nbsp;Ziaur Rahman&nbsp;(April 10, 1971 &ndash; May 15, 1971)</li>\r\n	<li>Captain Rafiqul Islam (June 10, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>Sectors Commanders:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rishimukh (Captain Shamsul Islam);</li>\r\n	<li>Sreenagar (Captain Matiur Rahman, Captain Mahfuzur Rahman);</li>\r\n	<li>Manughat (Captain Mahfuzur Rahman);</li>\r\n	<li>Tabalchhari (Sergeant Ali Hossain); and</li>\r\n	<li>Dimagiri (Army Sergeant, name unknown to date).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lance Nayek Munshi Abdur Rouf</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 22, '1479289775', '2016-11-16'),
(2, 'en', 'Sector 2', '<p><img alt="sector 2" src="img/sector/sector-2.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />Districts of Dhaka, Comilla, and Faridpur, and part of Noakhali District. The headquarters of sector 2 was at Melaghar.This sector has been under guerrilla war nearly 35 thousand. The number of regular troops were about 6 thousand. The sector as a result of forces between the Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Comilla and Feni completely expelled from the Pakistani army during the war in this area, and has the right to freedom. One of the main achievements of the sector in the &ldquo;Beloniya Sucibuzaha&rdquo; defense forces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Major&nbsp;Khaled Mosharraf&nbsp;(April 10, 1971 &ndash; September 22, 1971)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Major&nbsp;ATM Haider&nbsp;(September 22, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Sub</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>Sectors Commanders:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Gangasagar, Akhaura and Kasba (Mahbub, Lieutenant Farooq, and Lieutenant Humayun Kabir);</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Mandabhav (Captain Abdul hamid);</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Shalda-nadi (Mahmud Hasan);</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Matinagar (Lieutenant Didarul Alam);</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Nirbhoypur (Captain Akbar, Lieutenant Mahbub); and</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Rajnagar (Captain Jafar Imam, Captain Shahid, and Lieutenant Imamuzzaman)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Sepoy Mostofa Kamal</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 15, '1479289821', '2016-11-16'),
(3, 'en', 'Sector 3', '<p><img alt="Sector 3" src="img/sector/sector-3.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Area between Churaman Kathi (near Sreemangal) and&nbsp;Sylhet in the north and Singerbil of Brahmanbaria&nbsp;in the south. The headquarters of sector 2 was at Hezamara. Under this sector grew 19 guerrilla bases. November months, the number of guerrillas nearly thirty thousand. They are destroying some bridge in Comilla-Sylhet highway for disconnect the communication of Pak army. In Shayestaganj, they crash a train with the help of anti-tank mines. This was the most successful operation of this sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Major&nbsp;K. M. Shafiullah&nbsp;(April 10, 1971 &ndash; July 21, 1971)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Captain&nbsp;A. N. M. Nuruzzaman (July 23, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub</strong><strong>-</strong><strong>Sectors Commanders:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Asrambari (Captain Aziz, Captain Ejaz);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Baghaibari (Captain Aziz, Captain Ejaz);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Hatkata (Captain Matiur Rahman);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Simla (Captain Matin);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Panchabati (Captain Nasim);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Mantala (Captain MSA Bhuyan);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Vijoynagar (Captain MSA Bhuyan);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kalachhora (Lieutenant Majumdar);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kalkalia (Lieutenant Golam Helal Morshed); and</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bamutia (Lieutenant Sayeed)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>No Birsrestho in this sector</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 19, '1479289839', '2016-11-16'),
(4, 'en', 'Sector 4', '<p><img alt="" src="img/sector/sector-4.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />Area from&nbsp;Habiganj District&nbsp;on the north to Kanaighat Police Station on the south along the 100-mile-long border with&nbsp;India. The headquarters of sector 4 was initially at Karimganj and later at Masimpur. This sector was made with the EPR army of Sylhet and student freedom fighters. Number of Guerrilla army was 9 thousand and almost 4 thousand regular armies was here.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Major Chitta Ranjan Dutta (April 10, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Jalalpur (Mahbubur Rob Sadi);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barapunji (Captain A Rab &amp; Lieutenant Amirul Haque Chowdhury);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Amlasid (Lieutenant Zahir);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kukital (Flight Lieutenant Kader, Captain Shariful Haq);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kailas Shahar (Lieutenant Wakiuzzaman); and Fazlul Haque Chowdhury EX EPR (from April&#39;71 - August &#39;71)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Kamalpur (Captain Enam)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sepoy Hamidur Rahman</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 16, '1479289863', '2016-11-16'),
(5, 'en', 'Sector 5', '<p><img alt="sector 5" src="img/sector/sector-5.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />Area from Durgapur to Dawki (Tamabil) of&nbsp;Sylhet District&nbsp;and the entire area up to the eastern borders of the&nbsp;district. The headquarters of sector 5 was at Banshtola. This sector was made with 5 thousand guerrilla armies and 8 hundred regular armies. Most of the swamp areas of Sunamgonj and Chattak were included in this sector. Most successful operation of this sector was Chattak attack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Major&nbsp;Mir Shawkat Ali&nbsp;(April 10, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Muktapur (Captain Qazi Faruq Ahmed, Subsector Commander, 16 June 1971 till 1 February 1972; Subedar Mujibur Rahman, Second in Command; Nayeb Subedar Nazir Hussain, Admin in charge(non-combatant))</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Dawki (Subedar Major BR Chowdhury, (non-combatant));</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Shela (Captain Helal; Associate Lieutenant Commander Lieutenant Rahman and Abdur Rauf);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bholaganj (Lieutenant Taheruddin akhunji; Associate commander Lieutenant SM Khaled);</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Balat (Sergeant Ghani, Captain Salahuddin and Enamul Haq Chowdhury); and</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Barachhara (Captain Muslim Uddin).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Sangram Punji (Jaflong) (Captain Abdul Mutalib)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>No Birsrestho in this sector</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 16, '1479289900', '2016-11-16'),
(6, 'en', 'Sector 6', '<p><img alt="sector 6" src="img/sector/sector-6.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />This sector made with Rangpur District and part of Dinajpur District. The headquarters of sector 6 was at Burimari near Patgram. This was the only one sector which headquarter was in Bangladesh. In this sector, it was 7 hundred armies and it becomes almost 11 thousand until December. Of these, 2 thousand were regular armies and 9 thousand were Gono-bahini. This sector was occupied the northern Rangpur district by their forces.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Wing Commander M Khademul Bashar (April 10, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bhajanpur (Captain Nazrul, Flight&nbsp;Lieutenant Sadruddin and&nbsp;Captain&nbsp;Shahriyar)</li>\r\n	<li>Patgram (initially divided between&nbsp;junior commissioned officers of&nbsp;the EPR and later taken hold by&nbsp;Captain Matiur Rahman) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Sahebganj (Captain Nawazesh&nbsp;Uddin) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Phulbari, Kurigram (Captain Abul&nbsp;Hossain)</li>\r\n	<li>Mogalhat (Captain Delwar) and</li>\r\n	<li>Chilahati (Flight Lieutenant Iqbal)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No Birsrestho in this sector</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 10, '1479289919', '2016-11-16'),
(7, 'en', 'Sector 7', '<p><img alt="sector 7" src="img/sector/sector-7.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />This sector consists of Rajshahi, Pabna, Bogra and part of Dinajpur District. The headquarters of sector 7 was at Tarangpur near Balurghat. This sector is comprised of EPR soldiers. 12500 guerrilla armies consisting of 2500 regular soldiers were fight in this sector.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Major Nazmul Huq (April 10 &ndash; September 27, 1971)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Major Quazi nooruzzaman (September 30 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</li>\r\n	<li>Subedar Major A Rab</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Malan (initially divided between junior commissioned officers and later taken hold by Captain Mohiuddin Jahangir) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Tapan (Major Nazmul Huq, also commanded by commanding&nbsp;officers of the EPR) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Mehdipur (Subedar Iliyas, Captain Mahiuddin Jahangir) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Hamzapur (Captain Idris) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Anginabad (unnamed freedom fighter) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Sheikhpara (Captain Rashid) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Thokrabari (Subedar Muazzam) Í¾ and</li>\r\n	<li>Lalgola (Captain Gheyasuddin Chowdhury).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Captain Mahiuddin Jahangir</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 9, '1479289937', '2016-11-16'),
(8, 'en', 'Sector 8', '<p><img alt="sector 8" src="img/sector/sector-8.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />In April 1971, the operational area of the sector comprised the districts of Kushtia, Jessore, Khulna, Barisal, Faridpur and Patuakhali. At the end of May the sector was reconstituted and comprised the districts of Kuhstia, Jessore, Khulna, Satkhira and the northern part of Faridpur district. The headquarters of sector 8 was at Kolyanni. This sector was 3 thousand regular army and 25 thousand guerrilla army. In some areas, regular army establishing their own right and guerrilla armies build up some station inside Bangladesh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Major Abu Osman Chowdhury (April 10 &ndash; July 17, 1971)</li>\r\n	<li>Major Abul Manzoor (August 14, 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Boyra (Captain Khondakar Nazmul Huda) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Hakimpur (Captain Shafiq Ullah) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Bhomra (Captain Salahuddin, Captain Shahab Uddin) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Lalbazar (Captain AR Azam Chowdhury) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Banpur (Captain Mostafizur Rahman) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Benapole (Captain Abdul Halim, Captain Tawfiq&shy;-e-&shy;Elahi Chowdhury) and</li>\r\n	<li>Shikarpur (Captain Tawfiq&shy;-e-&shy;Elahi Chowdhury, Lieutenant Jahangir).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lance Nayek Nur Mohammad Sheikh</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 13, '1479289985', '2016-11-16'),
(9, 'en', 'Sector 9', '<p><img alt="sector 9" src="img/sector/sector-9.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />This sector build with Barisal, Patuakhali, and parts of the district of Khulna and Faridpur.The headquarters of sector 9 was at Taki near Boshirhat. Almost 20 thousand fighters fight in this sector. In December, the final month before the attack, this sector was merged with Sector 8 and is the major responsibility entrusted upon Major M. A Monzur.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Major M. A. Jalil (July 17 &ndash; December 24, 1971)</li>\r\n	<li>Major M. A Manzur</li>\r\n	<li>Major Joynal Abedin</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>TakiÍ¾</li>\r\n	<li>HingalganjÍ¾ and</li>\r\n	<li>Shamshernagar.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No Birsrestho in this sector</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 10, '1479290006', '2016-11-16'),
(10, 'en', 'Sector 10', '<p><img alt="sector 10" src="img/sector/sector-10.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />Sector 10 was constituted with the naval commandos. There is no regional boundaries. The organizer of this battalion was the 8 Bengalis of Pakistan Navy naval officer whose was training in France. They were Gazi Mohammad Rahmatullah (Chief Petty Officer), Syed Mosharraf Hossain (Petty Officer), Amin Ullah Sheikh (Petty Officer), Ahsan Ullah (ME-1), edabliucaudhuri (arao -1) Badiul Alam (ME-1), AR Mia (iena -1) and Abedura Rahman (Steward -1). Indian Navy gives them some training in river Zamuna near Delhi. Then some of the Pakistan Navy armies joined with them. 150 students selected from different sectors who are known as skilled swimmer and was sent for training camp. The bombing and destruction of vessels for use in limpet mines techniques are taught them. At the last moment, Indian commander M N Sumanta led this forces.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Commander HQ BD Forces (December 3&ndash;16, 1971)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>&bull;</strong>&nbsp;None.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Engineer Artificer Ruhul Amin</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 9, '1479290027', '2016-11-16'),
(11, 'en', 'Sector 11', '<p><img alt="sector 11" src="img/sector/sector-11.png" style="float:right; margin-left:10px; margin-right:10px" />This sector build with Mymensingh and Tangail along with parts of Rangpur &shy; Gaibandha, Ulipur, Kamalpur and Chilmari. The headquarters of sector 11 was at Teldhala until October 10, then transferred to Mahendraganj. About 25 thousand fighters fight in this sector. This sector is extensive guerrilla operations. The women in this sector up arms to fight against Pakistan armies. Moreover, Bangabir Kader Siddiqui organized 16 thousand guerrilla fighters in Tangail district and conducted several successful operations independently against Pakistan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sector Commander:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Major Ziaur Rahman (June 26, 1971 &ndash; October 10, 1971Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Major Abu Taher (October 10, 1971 &ndash; November 2, 1971(injured from mine blast) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Squadron Leader M. Hamidullah Khan) (November 2 , 1971 &ndash; February 14, 1972)<br />\r\n	&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sub Sectors (Commanders):</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Mankarchar (Flight Lt. M.&nbsp;Hamidullah Khan) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Mahendraganj (Captain Abu&nbsp;TaherÍ¾ Lieutenant Mannan) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Purakhasia (Lieutenant Hashem) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Dhalu (Lieutenant Taher AhmedÍ¾&nbsp;Lieutenant Kamal) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Rangra (Matiur Rahman)</li>\r\n	<li>Shivabari (divided between junior&nbsp;commissioned officers of the&nbsp;EPR) Í¾</li>\r\n	<li>Bagmara (divided between junior&nbsp;commissioned officers of the&nbsp;EPR) and</li>\r\n	<li>Maheshkhola (a member of the&nbsp;EPR).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Birsrestho of this sector:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No Birsrestho in this sector</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 9, '1479290052', '2016-11-16'),
